content: **Picture of a binocular microscope sitting on a wooden table, shot from a Canon EOS R camera with a 50mm f/1.8 lens, f/2.2 aperture, shutter speed 1/200s, ISO 100. Shiny metal surface reflects the light. The wooden table that the microscope sits on is weathered and aged, with deep cracks and grooves in the wood. A small drawer in the table is slightly open, showing some of its contents, there are some microscope glass slides and a few other small tools on the table, which add to the sense of mystery and intrigue. The scene is bathed in a warm, golden light, which seems to make everything glow, it looks like the photograph was taken during the late afternoon, with the sun casting long shadows across the table. A histology book is open at left. Viewer can almost feel the warmth of the sun on your skin. Hyper Realistic Photography, Cinematic, Cinema, Hyperdetail, Ultrahd, Color Correction, ultrahd, hdr.** - Upscaled by <@1076628899749957713> (fast)
